<title>INDIA: Foreign portfolio limit on 12 India firms to stay.</title>
<headline>Foreign portfolio limit on 12 India firms to stay.</headline>
<dateline>BOMBAY 1997-05-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>The ceiling on foreign institutional investor (FII) holdings stays on 12 Indian firms, the Reserve Bank of India (RBI) said on Tuesday.</p>
<p>The firms in which FII holdings have reached the ceiling of 24 percent are: Infosys Technologies, Housing Development Corp, Mastek Ltd, Satyam Computer Services Ltd, Polyplex Corp, Nagarjuna Construction, Pathega Forgings, Max India, Zee Telefilms, NIIT and Shivalik Projects.</p>
<p>FII holdings in state-run State Bank of India are also at the ceiling of 20 percent -- stipulated by the Indian government at the time of its government, the RBI said.</p>
<p>In Essel Packaging and Carrier Aircon, FII holdings have reached 20 percent of their equity and further purchases need RBI approval, the central bank said.</p>
<p>The 1997/98 (April-March) budget raised FII holding limits to 30 percent from 24 percent, but companies will require time to get shareholders' approval for the enhancement.</p>
